flowchart TD
    A[User submits query\nApp.tsx::handleRun] -->|Trimmed query payload\nWhy: begin streamed run| B[streamAgentRun\nsrc/frontend/src/utils/stream.ts::streamAgentRun]
    B -->|Per-frame callback\nRuntimeAgentStreamEvent| C[App.tsx::applyStreamEvent]
    C -->|heartbeat/status text\nWhy: immediate liveness feedback| D[runMessage state]
    C -->|progress step/status\nWhy: expose active execution stage| E[streamedProgress state]
    C -->|sub_queries list\nWhy: expose decomposition before completion| F[streamedSubQueries state]

    E --> G[ProgressHistory.tsx::ProgressHistory]
    F --> G
    G -->|Renders timeline + sub-query readout| H[System Progress panel]

    B -->|Completed payload\nagent_name/output/thread_id/sub_queries/tool_assignments| I[App.tsx::handleRun success path]
    I -->|Set answer only here\nWhy: enforce final-answer-after-completed| J[Final Readout answer]
    I -->|Set runDetails + finalized sub-queries| G

    B -->|Error result\nApiError contract| K[App.tsx::handleRun error path]
    K -->|Preserve submittedQuery + show deterministic message| L[Query readout + Run Status]

    M[Test trigger\nApp.test.tsx::"keeps query context..." ] -->|Asserts in-flight sub-query + no answer before resolve| H
    M -->|Resolves completion then asserts final answer appears| J

    N[Test trigger\nApp.test.tsx::"shows stream failure..." ] -->|Asserts query retained and retryable error shown| L

    O{{Tradeoff}}
    O --- O1[ProgressHistory prioritizes streamed in-flight state over runDetails for responsiveness.]
    O --- O2[On completion, App replaces streamed sub-queries with completed payload to avoid partial list drift.]
